Sure, here are five example sentences in Serbian that use the word "radost" in different forms and positions, along with their English translations:

1. *Radosti* nema ništa lepše na svetu od zagrljaja voljene osobe. (There is nothing more beautiful in the world than a hug from a loved one.)
2. Ona je ispunila moj dan *radosti* svojim osmehom. (She filled my day with joy with her smile.)
3. Sreća i *radost* su često posledica malih stvari u životu. (Happiness and joy are often the result of small things in life.)
4. *Radostan* sam što sam danas uspeo da završim sve obaveze. (I am happy that I managed to complete all my tasks today.)
5. Pesma koju smo slušali sinoć podsetila me je na neka stara vremena i donela mi *radost*. (The song we listened to last night reminded me of old times and brought me joy.)